[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you’ve been trying to keep character identity&nbsp; perfectly consistent while changing poses in Flux2&nbsp;&nbsp; Klein 9B, you know how quickly things can break.&nbsp; But look at this. By combining a reference image&nbsp;&nbsp; with a depth map, this new RefControl Depth LoRA&nbsp; lets you completely lock down facial features,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clothing, and style—while forcing the model&nbsp; to perfectly follow the structural depth of&nbsp;&nbsp; a brand new scene. Today, we’re going to look at&nbsp; exactly how it handles human portraits, complex&nbsp;&nbsp; object tracking, and how much you can push the&nbsp; weights to maintain perfect identity fidelity. &nbsp;'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Before we jump into the generation&nbsp; comparisons, here is a quick look at&nbsp;&nbsp; the Repo to see what this LoRA excels at,&nbsp; and how to get the cleanest results. &nbsp; The Core Use Cases are: Human portraits&nbsp; in different poses. Consistent character&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'design across multiple scenes. Object&nbsp; transformations (cars, furniture, props)&nbsp;&nbsp; with depth-guided placement. Storyboarding,&nbsp; comics, or animation frame generation. &nbsp; Tips for Best Results: Sweet Spot Weights:&nbsp; Keep your LoRA strength between 0.8 and 1.0.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Going lower loses identity, while going higher can&nbsp; cause harsh deep artifacts. Match Aspect Ratios:&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensure your reference image, depth map, and target&nbsp; resolution share the same aspect ratio to prevent&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stretched faces or distorted bodies. Leverage the&nbsp; Trigger Word: Always include the model\'s specific&nbsp;&nbsp; `refcontrol` trigger word alongside descriptive&nbsp; text prompts to smoothly blend your character into&nbsp;&nbsp; the new composition or backgrounds. Control the&nbsp; Background via Text: Use your prompt to dictate&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'changes in lighting, weather, and scenery; let&nbsp; the depth map handle the physical geometry. &nbsp; So, let\'s have a quick look at the workflow.&nbsp; This red note provides all links to the required&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'models. Download them and place them into the&nbsp; folders noted here. If you want to use the&nbsp;&nbsp; all-in-one merge file, you can download it from&nbsp; this link, and put it into the checkpoints folder&nbsp;&nbsp; under ComfyUI model\'s directory. It works great&nbsp; on my 12 gigabyte card. And follow this link to&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
